Functionality: common logic for serialization, will hold the includes, allow easily override serialization for the whole project (eg turn it off for some fork of nupic,...)

API:
```
import capnp...

__init__(type='capnp')
def serialize():
  if self.type == 'off':
    return
  return write()
def deserialize(obj):
  if self.type == 'off':
    return
  return read()
getType() # 'oldpy', 'capnp', 'off'
def write():
  raise # implment in your code
def read():
  raise # to implement
```

Classes: all that support, or should, serialization. Example: `MyClass: super(MyClass, self).__init__(type='off')`

